<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,982,1729]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1199,1225]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Notes.</emphasis>
This very rare species was described in 1876 based on the specimen(s) from the collection of Reiche (
<bibRefCitation author="Allard, E." pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref21895" refString="Allard, E. (1876) Revision des Helopines vrais de Lacordaire. L'Abeille, Journal d'Entomologie, 14, 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1876">Allard 1876</bibRefCitation>
) and redescribed in 1877 using the type specimen(s) and beetles collected by Leder (
<bibRefCitation author="Allard, E." box="[1212,1352,1235,1261]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="13 - 268" refId="ref21920" refString="Allard, E. (1877) Revision des Helopides vrais. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 5, 13 - 268." type="journal article" year="1877">Allard 1877</bibRefCitation>
). Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schneider, O. &amp; Leder, H." box="[151,445,1271,1297]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="3 - 262" refId="ref23434" refString="Schneider, O. &amp; Leder, H. (1878) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der kaukasischen Kaferfauna. Verhandlungen des Naturforschendes Vereines in Brunn, 16 (Supplementum), 3 - 262." type="journal article" year="1878">Schneider &amp; Leder (1878)</bibRefCitation>
again published Allard’s redescription 1877 and added the species’ type locality: “Elisa- betthal”. It was a settlement of German colonists, which is now called Asureti (
<collectingCountry box="[1037,1131,1307,1333]" name="Georgia" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Georgia</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1142,1278,1308,1335]" degrees="41" direction="north" minutes="35" orientation="latitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" precision="15" seconds="45" value="41.595833">41°35′45″N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1290,1425,1308,1335]" degrees="44" direction="east" minutes="40" orientation="longitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" precision="15" seconds="00" value="44.666668">44°40′00″E</geoCoordinate>
). Both description and redescription (
<bibRefCitation author="Allard, E." box="[547,685,1343,1369]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref21895" refString="Allard, E. (1876) Revision des Helopines vrais de Lacordaire. L'Abeille, Journal d'Entomologie, 14, 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1876">Allard 1876</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Allard, E." box="[694,751,1343,1369]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="13 - 268" refId="ref21920" refString="Allard, E. (1877) Revision des Helopides vrais. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 5, 13 - 268." type="journal article" year="1877">1877</bibRefCitation>
) have differences, and the latter is more consistent with specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[282,372,1379,1405]" name="Georgia" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Georgia</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[531,632,1379,1405]" name="Armenia" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, as mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Abdurakhmanov, G. M. &amp; Nabozhenko, M. V." box="[839,1293,1379,1405]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refId="ref21743" refString="Abdurakhmanov, G. M. &amp; Nabozhenko, M. V. (2011) Keys and catalogue to darkling beetles (Coleoptera: Tenebrionidae s. str.) of the Caucasus and south of European part of Russia. KMK Scientific Press Ltd, Moscow, 361 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="2011">Abdurakhmanov &amp; Nabozhenko (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. In addition, the Russian authors erroneously interpreted species from South 
<collectingCountry box="[872,970,1415,1441]" name="Armenia" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Armenia</collectingCountry>
and Nakhchivan as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Allard" authorityYear="1876" box="[1200,1311,1415,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Helops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinus">
<emphasis box="[1200,1311,1415,1440]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">E. vicinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(described below as 
<taxonomicName authority="Nabozhenko, 2022" authorityName="Nabozhenko" authorityYear="2022" box="[259,409,1451,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Euboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kalashiani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[259,409,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">E. kalashiani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[417,506,1451,1477]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) since Bogachev (1938). As a result, Abdurakhmanov &amp; Nabozhenko described a new species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nabozhenko et Abdurakhmanov" authorityYear="2011" box="[294,542,1487,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Probaticus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medvedevi">
<emphasis box="[294,542,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Probaticus medvedevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[720,818,1487,1513]" name="Armenia" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Armenia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[833,959,1487,1513]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1851,1875]" captionTargetBox="[213,1377,185,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-32@8.[208,1380,181,1827]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Euboeus vicinus, habitus, labels, details of structure. A = male dorsally (Georgia, Asureti); B = female dorsally (Georgia, Asureti); C = female dorsally (Georgia, Asureti); D = female dorsally (Armenia, Alaverdi), holotype of Probaticus medvedevi; E = labels of non-type specimens from Georgia, Asureti (HNHM); F = labels of the holotype of Probaticus medvedevi; G = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; H = spiculum gastrale; I = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; J = tegmen, ventrally; K = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Figs 6D, F</figureCitation>
). Allard examined the specimens of Leder and confirmed that they belong to his species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Allard" authorityYear="1876" box="[695,864,1523,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Helops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinus">
<emphasis box="[695,864,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Helops vicinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as he wrote in redescription (
<bibRefCitation author="Allard, E." box="[1226,1370,1523,1549]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="13 - 268" refId="ref21920" refString="Allard, E. (1877) Revision des Helopides vrais. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 5, 13 - 268." type="journal article" year="1877">Allard 1877</bibRefCitation>
). The Leder’s specimens (
<figureCitation box="[373,597,1559,1585]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1851,1875]" captionTargetBox="[213,1377,185,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-32@8.[208,1380,181,1827]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Euboeus vicinus, habitus, labels, details of structure. A = male dorsally (Georgia, Asureti); B = female dorsally (Georgia, Asureti); C = female dorsally (Georgia, Asureti); D = female dorsally (Armenia, Alaverdi), holotype of Probaticus medvedevi; E = labels of non-type specimens from Georgia, Asureti (HNHM); F = labels of the holotype of Probaticus medvedevi; G = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; H = spiculum gastrale; I = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; J = tegmen, ventrally; K = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Figs 6A–C, E, G–K</figureCitation>
) are not 
<typeStatus box="[693,791,1559,1585]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">syntypes</typeStatus>
(as marked on the labels) because the original description was based on other specimens from the Reiche collection. The females from 
<collectingCountry box="[1016,1106,1595,1621]" name="Georgia" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Georgia</collectingCountry>
are conspecific to the female (
<typeStatus box="[159,260,1631,1657]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">holotype</typeStatus>
) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nabozhenko et Abdurakhmanov" authorityYear="2011" box="[308,458,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Probaticus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medvedevi">
<emphasis box="[308,458,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">E. medvedevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
despite the variability. As a result, I propose the following synonymy: 
<taxonomicName authority="Allard, 1876" authorityName="Allard" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Helops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinus">
<emphasis box="[1269,1436,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Helops vicinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Allard, E." box="[151,293,1667,1693]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref21895" refString="Allard, E. (1876) Revision des Helopines vrais de Lacordaire. L'Abeille, Journal d'Entomologie, 14, 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1876">Allard, 1876</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName authority="Abdurakhmanov et Nabozhenko, 2011" authorityName="Abdurakhmanov et Nabozhenko" authorityYear="2011" box="[323,1145,1667,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Probaticus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medvedevi" status="syn. nov." subGenus="Pelorinus">
<emphasis box="[323,445,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Probaticus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[461,570,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Pelorinus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[586,704,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">medvedevi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Abdurakhmanov, G. M. &amp; Nabozhenko, M. V." box="[709,1145,1667,1693]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" refId="ref21743" refString="Abdurakhmanov, G. M. &amp; Nabozhenko, M. V. (2011) Keys and catalogue to darkling beetles (Coleoptera: Tenebrionidae s. str.) of the Caucasus and south of European part of Russia. KMK Scientific Press Ltd, Moscow, 361 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="2011">Abdurakhmanov et Nabozhenko, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1156,1260,1667,1693]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1156,1260,1667,1693]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,861,1702,1729]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,982,1729]" box="[199,861,1702,1729]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1702,1728]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Distribution.</emphasis>
Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[468,561,1703,1729]" name="Georgia" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Georgia</collectingCountry>
, northern area of 
<collectingCountry box="[755,857,1703,1729]" name="Armenia" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Armenia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
